We can sit around and be satisfied with our bg control and assume that
it will prevent all the bg-related complications and any other nasty
effects of diabetes.

But no research has shown that diabetics with excellent blood sugar
control are at zero risk for complications and heart disease and all
the other things. In fact, all the research has shown that we're still
at increased risk even with excellent control.

If the NYT article came out heavy on the pharma side, that's
unfortunate. It doesn't mean that we're off the hook. Me, whatever I
can do to lessen all the other risks, I'll try it, whether it's a pill
or (more often) something else. And I realize fully that I'm still not
doing everything I could.

