The current research proves that higher HDL and lower TGLs are far more
predictive of CVD than LDL and that the target of very low LDL is an
inappropriate recommendation.

But targets aren't the only consideration: it's *how* you get your bg
and lipids to goals that's important.  Eating and living in a way that
achieves goals is far more protective because you're not fighting
damaging processes with chemical interventions.

